# TASK 9: Tinkercad
## Objectives
The goal was to master the Tinkercad environment by simulating a radar system and a digital parking assistant. I aimed to interface an ultrasonic sensor with a servo motor to detect obstacles and apply Pulse Width Modulation (PWM) to provide visual proximity alerts.
## Outcomes
- gained proficiency in using Tinkercad for virtual circuit prototyping and real-time simulation.
- mastered the working principles of ultrasonic sensors, specifically calculating distance based on sound wave travel time.
- implemented servo motor control to expand the sensor's detection field, mimicking radar technology.
- developed logical sequences using PWM to trigger LED indicators based on proximity thresholds.
- practiced troubleshooting Arduino C++ code and utilizing serial monitor data for sensor calibration.
Click [here](https://www.tinkercad.com/things/8avVG2PzllG-mighty-krunk-kup) to check out the stimulation for this task

# TASK 10: Speed Control of DC Motor
## Objectives
the goal was to master DC motor control using an Arduino Uno and the L298N driver. I aimed to simulate and then implement a hardware circuit to programmatically regulate the speed and direction of a 5V BO motor.
## Outcomes
- mastered H-bridge logic to control bidirectional motor rotation by swapping polarity.
- implemented PWM via analogWrite() for precise RPM regulation.
- resolved hardware constraints, including establishing a common ground and managing L298N voltage drops.
- practiced troubleshooting by removing ENA jumpers to enable software-based speed control.
![alt text](https://youtube.com/shorts/Bvt_IgRtIvE)

