# TASK 13:
## Objectives
the aim was to build a 555 astable multivibrator generating a 60% duty cycle square wave to understand the relationships between R1, R2, and C components.
## Outcomes
- Theory: derived R1 = 0.5 \times R2 to achieve the specific 60% duty cycle requirement.
- Construction: gained hands-on experience building the R-C network on a breadboard.
- Analysis: Using a DSO, I verified the output at Pin 3 and analyzed capacitor charge/discharge curves.
- Troubleshooting: learned to optimize wiring to minimize parasitic capacitance.
![Alt Text](https://github.com/niharika526/level-0/blob/main/555%20multivibrator%201.jpeg?raw=true)
![Alt Text](https://github.com/niharika526/level-0/blob/main/555%20multivibrator%202.jpeg?raw=true)

# TASK 14: Karnaugh Maps and Deriving the logic circuit
## Objectives
The aim was to design and simulate a logic-based security system using Karnaugh Maps. My goal was to translate the Boolean expression Y = A \cdot \bar{B} into a functional circuit using logic gate ICs on a virtual breadboard.
## Outcomes
- Logic Synthesis: I successfully implemented 74HC08 and 74HC04 chips, mapping truth tables to physical pin configurations.
- Hardware Management: I mastered stable input signaling and correctly biased IC power pins for stability.
- Troubleshooting: I used signal tracing to isolate errors and learned to use transistors for driving high-load components like buzzers.
